description: The BMO Long Federal Bond Index ETF has been designed to replicate, to the extent possible, the performance of the FTSE TMX Canada Long Term Federal Bond IndexTM, net of expenses. The Fund invests in a variety of debt securities primarily with a term to maturity greater than ten years. Securities held in the Index are generally issued or guaranteed by the Government of Canada, by various agencies of the Government of Canada, and by various instrumentalities that have been established or sponsored by the Government of Canada.
name: BMO Long Federal Bond Index ETF
